3) Experiment 3 — Practice Source Code Management on GitHub (step-by-step + deploy)
Aim: Put your Program 1 code under Git version control, push to GitHub, create branch, create PR, merge.

Step-by-step (commands + UI steps):

Prepare local folder

cd path/to/your/project   # folder with registration.html
echo "# simple-register" > README.md
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit: registration form"
Create repo on GitHub

Go to https://github.com → New → name simple-register → Create.

Link and push

git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/<your-username>/simple-register.git
git push -u origin main
Output looks like the git push sample in Experiment 2.

Create feature branch, make changes locally

git checkout -b add-college
# edit registration.html (add <input placeholder="College">)
git add registration.html
git commit -m "Add College field"
git push -u origin add-college
Open Pull Request

On GitHub repo page → Compare & pull request → give title → Create pull request → Review → Merge.

Merge & sync

After merging, locally:

git checkout main
git pull origin main
How to deploy front-end HTML on GitHub Pages (quick):

On GitHub → Settings → Pages → Source: main / root → Save → open https://<you>.github.io/simple-register/.
